    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p><em><strong>Two roles.</strong> (1) Optional <em>duel</em> by the shrine steps — a fast, parry-heavy katana master who teaches the defensive game and drops 800 souls + a fine blade if bested (disposition starts neutral; he turns hostile only if challenged). (2) The <strong>mercy valve</strong>: after repeated wipes, the DM may drop him as a <em>controllable ally token</em> (a summon sign answered) to steady a struggling party for one fight. Set his disposition to friendly when summoned.</em></p><p><strong>Moveset (full Defensive Profiles in the DM Codex):</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Iaido Double-Slash</strong> (2 x 1d8+4): dodge ADV W2; parry ADV only on W3 (the second cut).</li><li><strong>Parry Stance</strong> (reaction): he parries the next melee attack you telegraph — feint or go unorthodox.</li><li><strong>Step Thrust</strong> (reach 1d10+4): sidestep the line W1; parry ADV W2.</li></ul><p><strong>Tell Ladder:</strong> (1) he reads obvious swings — mix your timing; (2) his double-slash over-commits on the second cut; (3) he's a teacher, not a wall — patience wins.</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
